A MAN TOLD HIS STORY ABOUT GROWING UP LIVING IN THE LIBRARY. WHEN HE WAS REALLY LITTLE, AT THE DINNER TABLE, HE TOLD HID PARENTS "I'M SO GLAD WE'RE RICH", AND THE PARENTS TOLD HIM THEY WERE POOR.
THE DAD THEN GOT A JOB CLEANING THE LOCAL LIBRARY, AND THEY MOVED IN TO THE APARTMENT ON TOP.
HIS DAD KEPT THE LIBRARY SPOTLESS - EVERYTHING WAS SWEPT AND MOPPED AND WAXED.
THE BOY WAS EMBARRASSED ABOUT LIVING THERE AT FIRST - HE JUST WANTED TO LIVE IN A HOUSE LIKE A NORMAL KID - BUT HE GREW TO LOVE IT.
LIVING IN THE LIBRARY ENRICHED HIS EDUCATION.
HE ENDED UP BEING THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL, THE GRADUATE COLLEGE.
HE MOVED ON TO BE A COLLEGE PROFESSOR- HIS DAD WAS SO PROUD OF HIM.
HE CREDITS HIS SUCCESSES TO HAVING GROWN UP IN THE LIBRARRY.
